%I A395546 #22 Jun 12 2026 22:21:16
%S A395546 36,35744,5217190,222446648,4475836024,54647284328,466883298042
%N A395546 Number of satisfiable 3-SAT formulas with n variables and 5 clauses in the multiset clause model.
%C A395546 Clauses are multisets of 3 literals chosen from {x_1, ..., x_n, not x_1, ..., not x_n}; repeated literals inside a clause are allowed. A formula is a multiset of 5 such clauses, so repeated clauses are also allowed.
%C A395546 Together with A396491, this sequence partitions the set of all 5-clause formulas in the same multiset model into satisfiable and unsatisfiable formulas.
%D A395546 Stephen A. Cook, The complexity of theorem-proving procedures, Proceedings of the Third Annual ACM Symposium on Theory of Computing, 1971, 151-158.
%F A395546 a(n) = binomial(binomial(2*n+2,3)+4,5) - A396491(n).
%F A395546 Using the conjectured formula for A396491, a(n) = binomial(binomial(2*n+2,3)+4,5) - (129332*n^6 - 2237100*n^5 + 16427761*n^4 - 63136975*n^3 + 130884126*n^2 - 135887564*n + 53820480)/3.
%Y A395546 Cf. A396351, A396491, A396492, A396493.
%K A395546 nonn,hard,more
%O A395546 1,1
%A A395546 _Ramin Mohammadi Masoudi_, Jun 01 2026
